contentrichtext.text: '''Johnson Creek''' may refer to many places in the United States, including: * [[Johnson Creek, Wisconsin]], a village in southern Wisconsin * [[Johnson Creek (Rock River tributary)]], a stream in southern Wisconsin * [[Johnson Creek (Texas)]], a tributary in the Trinity River watershed in North Texas * [[Johnson Creek (Willamette River)]], a tributary of the Willamette River in Oregon * [[Johnson Creek (Tualatin River)]], a tributary of the [[Tualatin River]] in Oregon * [[Johnson Creek (Georgia)]], part of the Intracoastal Waterway, [http://geonames.usgs.gov/pls/gnispublic/f?p=gnispq:3:::NO::P3_FID:342347 USGS Feature Detail Report] ==See also== * [[Ardenwald-Johnson Creek, Portland, Oregon]] * [[Johnson Creek Airport]] {{disamb}} [[Category:Place name disambiguation pages]]
